    <h1>Read Faster — Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: March 2026</p>

    <p>
      Read Faster is designed with your privacy in mind. We do not collect,
      store, or transmit any personal data.
    </p>

    <h2>Data Storage</h2>
    <p>
      All data — including imported books, reading progress, bookmarks, and
      preferences — is stored locally on your device using Apple's SwiftData
      framework. No data leaves your device.
    </p>

    <h2>No Analytics or Tracking</h2>
    <p>
      Read Faster does not include any analytics SDKs, advertising frameworks,
      or tracking mechanisms. We do not collect usage data, crash reports, or
      device identifiers.
    </p>

    <h2>No Network Requests</h2>
    <p>
      The app operates entirely offline. It does not connect to any server or
      third-party service. No internet connection is required.
    </p>

    <h2>No Account Required</h2>
    <p>Read Faster does not require you to create an account or sign in.</p>

    <h2>Third-Party Libraries</h2>
    <p>
      The app uses ZIPFoundation (for EPUB extraction) and SwiftSoup (for HTML
      parsing). These libraries operate entirely on-device and do not transmit
      data.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      If you have questions about this policy, contact us at
      <a href="mailto:jjalangtry@gmail.com">jjalangtry@gmail.com</a>.
    </p>
  </body>
